CSS --> Cascade Style Sheet
It provides us the properties which you can apply on your html pages to make it more attractive

We can implement CSS in three ways
1. Inline
    <h1 style="property1:value1;property2:value2;">This is very nice</h1>
    <h1 style='color : red'>This is CSS</h1>
    <h1 style='color : red; fontsize : 40px'>This is H1 Tag</h1>
2. Internal
    It is applied in head Tag
    <head>
        <style>
            tag_name1, tag_name2, tag_name3....{
                property1 : value;
                property2 : value;
            }
            .main{
                color : red;
                font-family : monospace;
            }
            li, .main{
                backgroundcolor : white;
            }
            #p1{
                font-style : "italic";
            }
    <body>
        <h1 class="main"> This is heading 1 </h1>
        <p class="main"> This is paragraph tag </p>
        <li> List1 </li>
        <p id="p1"> Python is awesome </p>
    <body>
    tag_name {
        p1 : v1;
    }
    .class_name{
        p1 : v1;
    }
    #id_name{
        p1 : v1;
    }
3. External

difference between px and %???